content:
The Share Visit setting is scheduled for retirement in Spring '25. After the upgrade to Spring '25, you can no longer see the Share visits feature under Retail Execution Settings in Setup and visit access will be available only for the users who created the visit as per the platform's behavior.

You can implement custom sharing by using the platform's sharing capabilities such as sharing rules and role-based hierarchy or change the ownership of the visit record to the appropriate user. To avoid loss of visit data, complete the required custom sharing implementation and turn off the share visit setting before the Spring '25 upgrade.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions where Consumer Goods Cloud is enabled.
